Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[As late as 2011 the Philippines were estimated to be among the top 10 rabies hotspot in Asia. More recently there have successful efforts in some parts of the country to improve the situation by enhanced dog rabies control programmes and increasing awareness of the general population. The unfortunate death of the person in this report can be attributed to a delay in administration of post-exposure prophylaxis due to the victim's reluctance to seek treatment when such treatment was available. Education of the population to the risk of rabies virus infection remains a priority in Cotabato at least.

Kidapawan City is a city in the province of Cotabato, Philippines. It is the capital city of Cotabato Province. It is a favorite tourist destination in the late October to December and in the summer. Tourists should be alerted to the risk of exposure to rabies virus infection at this destination. The location of Cotabato province and Kidapawan city can be found in the interactive HealthMap at: http://healthmap.org/r/2msp. - Mod.CP]
